# Installation guide for the latest version of Sass

This guide will walk you through installing the latest version of Sass for your project.

## Step 1: Open your terminal

Open your command prompt or terminal.

## Step 2: Navigate to your project folder

Use the `cd` command to navigate to your project folder.
For example:
cd "C:\Users\HP\Desktop\ALX\Projects ALX\alx-intermediate-frontend\0x03-sass_scss"

## Step 3: Install Sass

Run the following command to install the latest version of Sass and add it to your project's devDependencies.

npm install sass --save-dev

## Step 4: Verify the installation

After the installation is complete, you can check your `package.json` file. You should see `sass` listed under `devDependencies` with the installed version.

You can also check the installed version by running:
npm view sass version
